                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d913">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">390D.11/184: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-21T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 21, 1939—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>147. Your telegram No. 53, November 20, 6 p.m.<note n="13" xml:id="d913fn13">Not
                        printed.</note> The Foreign Office has informally submitted to us a
                    counterproposal which however is quite at variance with our ideas in a number of
                    points and requires considerable discussion before we can contemplate its taking
                    a form that we could submit for your approval.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
